cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with visual element discovery and pattern mining using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as association rule mining, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of CNNs for feature extraction and classification also relates to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper applies the proposed approach to scene and object classification tasks, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
